A city's police force which was tasked to weed out the abuse of vulnerable women has arrested 54 people in just a month.

Officers in Newcastle set up Operation Sanctuary to comb through taxi firms, B&Bs and takeaways to find people who have been sexually exploited.

Since the launch they have already identified around 80 women and girls who may be victims.

