Twenty-seven people - 25 men and two women - were arrested in the first week at the end of last month and the tip-offs have been coming in steadily since, a Northumbria Police spokesman said.

One man has been charged with raping an underage girl after allegations emerged as part of the operation.

Abdul Jelilou Ouro Kefia, 21, from Walker, Newcastle, was charged with one count of rape of a female under 16 after the alleged incident on February 17.

